section.section:
The Office shall:
carry out an energy emergency crisis intervention program to prevent low-income households, including the near poor, the elderly, households with children, and those on fixed incomes from experiencing danger to health or survival as a result of an energy emergency;
establish intake procedures for those experiencing an energy emergency;
establish guidelines for the income and program eligibility of applicants; and
identify local public or private agencies to administer the crisis intervention program.
